      "text": "A 56-year-old man comes to your clinic with throat pain and progressive difficulty swallowing food for the past 5 months. He also reports intermittent left ear pain for the past 3 months. His medical history is significant for hypertension, managed with amlodipine. His father died of laryngeal cancer at age 55. He has a 36-year history of smoking one pack of cigarettes daily and drinks 2–3 beers daily. Vital signs are normal. On examination, there is left cervical lymphadenopathy. Oropharyngeal examination reveals a 3-cm ulcerating mass on the left tonsil. Examination of both auditory canals is normal. Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial step in management?",
