      "correct_choice_id": 5,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=hl0c9T&anker=Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-learningcard-id=\"hl0c9T\" data-anker=\"Zea67157b231e5e1dc4f88251b1e79823\" data-section-id=\"NCX-HZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"2ZbTaH\">Laryngoscopy</a> would help assess any concurrent masses in the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Zdc6918bc99931ac9e8b52ff7eb53beda\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Zdc6918bc99931ac9e8b52ff7eb53beda\">larynx</a>, but it would not allow for evaluation of this patient's tonsillar mass nor any other potential primary sites outside of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T6064S&anker=Zdc6918bc99931ac9e8b52ff7eb53beda\" data-learningcard-id=\"T6064S\" data-anker=\"Zdc6918bc99931ac9e8b52ff7eb53beda\">larynx</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<span data-sememe-id=\"Ngb-vG\">Esophagoscopy</span> would be used to assess for any concurrent masses in the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=f60k4S&anker=Zbef3d9b02e684352759e6e1de6190d7a\" data-learningcard-id=\"f60k4S\" data-anker=\"Zbef3d9b02e684352759e6e1de6190d7a\">esophagus</a>. However, it would not help further evaluate this patient's tonsillar mass. Other potential primary sites of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z17c54b50884f6ae691e10c71ea7eccb6\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z17c54b50884f6ae691e10c71ea7eccb6\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"prXLRz\">SCC</a> should be identified as well, but these may not be limited to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=f60k4S&anker=Zbef3d9b02e684352759e6e1de6190d7a\" data-learningcard-id=\"f60k4S\" data-anker=\"Zbef3d9b02e684352759e6e1de6190d7a\">esophagus</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>A <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=D501mg&anker=Zf437f75c80b33a3539ab8aa076e35437\" data-learningcard-id=\"D501mg\" data-anker=\"Zf437f75c80b33a3539ab8aa076e35437\" data-sememe-id=\"Wo0PaS\">barium swallow</a> is used to evaluate <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=vg0AC2&anker=Z2366f5f264ce3ede806bbc0085041077\" data-learningcard-id=\"vg0AC2\" data-anker=\"Z2366f5f264ce3ede806bbc0085041077\" data-section-id=\"k80m53\" data-sememe-id=\"uG0pa3\">gastroesophageal reflux</a>, assess a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=vH0AHh&anker=Z110d4126c6c4e2cb567242f4c0f4a60d\" data-learningcard-id=\"vH0AHh\" data-anker=\"Z110d4126c6c4e2cb567242f4c0f4a60d\" data-sememe-id=\"gzbFHw\">fistula</a> or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Dg01x2&anker=Z496ee96043ad1b953dc0742fd7a99ab4\" data-learningcard-id=\"Dg01x2\" data-anker=\"Z496ee96043ad1b953dc0742fd7a99ab4\" data-sememe-id=\"fzYkH7\">hiatal hernia</a>, or identify the cause of persistent <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7J04vS&anker=Z2f0b48ef2acaab783b03e4c8d2404f90\" data-learningcard-id=\"7J04vS\" data-anker=\"Z2f0b48ef2acaab783b03e4c8d2404f90\">vomiting</a> or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=D501mg&anker=Zd2d195657240f493374e95e2b75cc8cf\" data-learningcard-id=\"D501mg\" data-anker=\"Zd2d195657240f493374e95e2b75cc8cf\" data-section-id=\"-ZXDV9\" data-sememe-id=\"IQ0Yxf\">dysphagia</a>. However, the cause of this patient's <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=D501mg&anker=Zd2d195657240f493374e95e2b75cc8cf\" data-learningcard-id=\"D501mg\" data-anker=\"Zd2d195657240f493374e95e2b75cc8cf\" data-section-id=\"-ZXDV9\" data-sememe-id=\"IQ0Yxf\">dysphagia</a> has already been identified (a tonsillar mass). As this patient has <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=do0oaS&anker=Zd683b39cdd22e209ef414f798da53d44\" data-learningcard-id=\"do0oaS\" data-anker=\"Zd683b39cdd22e209ef414f798da53d44\">cervical lymphadenopathy</a> and known <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ps0LDh&anker=Zbc0d0ff153bc5c7a27589815d0c842fd\" data-learningcard-id=\"ps0LDh\" data-anker=\"Zbc0d0ff153bc5c7a27589815d0c842fd\" data-section-id=\"FfWgLk0\" data-sememe-id=\"b31HSg0\">risk factors</a> for oropharyngeal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z17c54b50884f6ae691e10c71ea7eccb6\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z17c54b50884f6ae691e10c71ea7eccb6\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"prXLRz\">SCC</a>, further workup of the tonsillar mass and assessment for other masses in the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=b60HjS&anker=Za8f78934b39668c36b884a3002afaebe\" data-learningcard-id=\"b60HjS\" data-anker=\"Za8f78934b39668c36b884a3002afaebe\">head and neck region</a> are indicated.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<span data-sememe-id=\"94bNlF\">Nasopharyngoscopy</span> would help further evaluate this patient's tonsillar mass and assess for other <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=es0xFh&anker=Z1999c130bd7c131bbea9b7d680230c63\" data-learningcard-id=\"es0xFh\" data-anker=\"Z1999c130bd7c131bbea9b7d680230c63\" data-section-id=\"McWM140\">nasopharyngeal</a> masses. However, it would not help identify other potential primary sites of cancer outside of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=es0xFh&anker=Z1999c130bd7c131bbea9b7d680230c63\" data-learningcard-id=\"es0xFh\" data-anker=\"Z1999c130bd7c131bbea9b7d680230c63\" data-section-id=\"McWM140\">nasopharynx</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) CORRECT:</h4>\n<span class=\"wichtig\"><b><span data-sememe-id=\"w4bhlF\">Panendoscopy</span></b></span> allows for comprehensive evaluation of the entire <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pu0Wr3&anker=Z0f718e4f6cdcb36f44fefaee99468e82\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pu0Wr3\" data-anker=\"Z0f718e4f6cdcb36f44fefaee99468e82\" data-section-id=\"7dd4rK0\" data-sememe-id=\"cgWa8k0\">upper airway</a> and digestive tract and is indicated in all patients with suspected <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Cj0qcT&anker=Z4ba9a83278a5fb4356bd0e4dcc25f0a2\" data-learningcard-id=\"Cj0qcT\" data-anker=\"Z4ba9a83278a5fb4356bd0e4dcc25f0a2\" data-section-id=\"mOYVG6\" data-sememe-id=\"ojX0Yy\">oropharyngeal cancer</a> and a <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>high risk for second primary tumors </b></span>(e.g., due to heavy smoking, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=En08Eg&anker=Z0ccd21fcf57fab20ffb12c037f4d9af3\" data-learningcard-id=\"En08Eg\" data-anker=\"Z0ccd21fcf57fab20ffb12c037f4d9af3\" data-section-id=\"ol10BS0\">family history</a> of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Po0WXS&anker=Zdfb1e1ac048afa677c2adfea5a80f375\" data-learningcard-id=\"Po0WXS\" data-anker=\"Zdfb1e1ac048afa677c2adfea5a80f375\" data-sememe-id=\"L1awhj\">oral cancer</a>). <span data-sememe-id=\"sebtZG\">Biopsies</span> of any masses would also be taken during or following the <span data-sememe-id=\"w4bhlF\">panendoscopy</span> for histological evaluation.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point:</b></span> <span data-sememe-id=\"w4bhlF\">Panendoscopy</span> is the initial evaluation of choice for suspected <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Cj0qcT&anker=Z4ba9a83278a5fb4356bd0e4dcc25f0a2\" data-learningcard-id=\"Cj0qcT\" data-anker=\"Z4ba9a83278a5fb4356bd0e4dcc25f0a2\" data-section-id=\"mOYVG6\" data-sememe-id=\"ojX0Yy\">oropharyngeal cancer</a> to assess for synchronous primary tumors in the upper aerodigestive tract, especially in patients with significant <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ps0LDh&anker=Zbc0d0ff153bc5c7a27589815d0c842fd\" data-learningcard-id=\"ps0LDh\" data-anker=\"Zbc0d0ff153bc5c7a27589815d0c842fd\" data-section-id=\"FfWgLk0\" data-sememe-id=\"b31HSg0\">risk factors</a>.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_508c11f50b0de.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>Exophytic lesion of the left tonsil</p></div></div></div>",
